I LOVED the show SO much more than last year, but of course I still think it can be drastically improved. What I think could be improved: 1) The show would be far better if it was at the end of November or early December to play into the holiday season vibes/cheerfulness. 2) It needs to be WAY MORE upbeat/energetic/fast paced. 3) Some of the models felt too serious for this kind of show/production. The show has been on a steady improvement back to what it once was, but it still feels stiff, if that makes sense. Just make it more fun. 4) More cinematic shots/scenes during the breaks in between segments/themes. 5) More definitive "themes". I didn't understand what the themes were supposed to be until the end so maybe an introduction/title card would help too. 6) Keep it classy and glamourous. Especially backstage... please. Angels are supposed to be on a pedestal for a reason, and some etiquette could be improved. 7) Less jeans and denim and more new lingerie or even pajamas. When I went on the website to shop the show, there was hardly anything "new" that I hadn't seen in the last year. (Also please do get rid of that ugly Shein belt that was on all the denim) 8) The models needed to be at a faster pace or closer together. There was too much time and space between each model, and it seemed like the cameras didn't know who or where to focus on in between each model. 9) This is truly my opinion, but I think the performers should be performing while the girls are walking and not entirely separately. (I loved the last performance but the entire time I was waiting for the models and was disappointed when they didn't come out) Loved Madison Beer's performance tho, and that was phenomenal to me. 10) BRING BACK THE CAMERA THAT GLIDES ALONG THE RUNWAY. 11) Dear God, what was going on during the Pink segment? I loved that they brought it back but that sequin jacket... yikes. I haven't seen anyone actually wear one of those since like 2010 (and I don't mean that in a good way) 12) Maybe bring back the glitter runway? It seems like the models got better traction on there and it was just more fun and prettier overall. 13) More backstage shots of the models dancing, laughing, and having a good time! What I loved: 1) The cinematic opening. Holy moly, that brought back so many memories of my teen years watching the shows and it made me cry. 2) The pink carpet / backstage area. Twas an emotional night for me because I sobbed when I saw they fully brought it back. 3) THE MAKEUP and blowouts of course. The makeup was truly stunning and made the older angels truly glow. 4) I loved how the stage was raised again and separate from the audience. 5) I loved how so much effort was put into SOME of the outfits and wings. Felt like those outfits were so glamorous and artistic again! That's all for now and I can't wait for next year!

And alot of the looks didn't hit the mark for me. The classy/fully clothed moments made the lingerie/sexy elements feel cheep/too revealing. I feel like they didn't properly marry their new brand with the old brand. Would've may been better to have sections of the show that were full outfits and sections that were all lingerie. This missed the mark for me.

She has so much potential and is still so underrated. Candice is divine, the best body on earth. Adriana‚Äôs body looks incredible. She recovered so well after her pregnancy, but her walk was‚Ä¶ meh. Very careless, not sexy at all. Alessandra looked unchanged, as stunning as ever. Doutzen was awesome, even though her face has become so slim that she almost doesn‚Äôt look like herself anymore. She used to have that sweet look, which I can‚Äôt really find in her now. The disappointment for me was Joan Smalls. What‚Äôs with those lips? She was so pretty before. Yasmin Wijnaldum and Irina Shayk deserved much better outfits. Gigi Hadid once again proved she can‚Äôt walk properly with heavy props or wings. Even though I love her and her features, she has a great body and face. The one who stole the show was Bella Hadid. She has improved her walk and her looks so much; she looked impeccable. My number two favorite, right after Candice in this show. And let‚Äôs not forget Behati, loved her flawless walk as always. She‚Äôs getting even better with age. Barbara Palvin, sweet and natural as always. Anok, another great presence on stage. It‚Äôs sad they didn‚Äôt bring back Sara Sampaio, Lais Ribeiro, and Romee Strijd; they were the true successors of the old-school supermodels, with huge potential. And Vanessa Cerutti, too. I would have loved to see also some of the show‚Äôs legends walking again, like Gisele, Karolina, and Carmen Kass. And Izabel Goulart as well, she‚Äôs aging like fine wine. Maybe even Lindsay Ellingson, for her angelic face. She‚Äôs a mom of three now, but still looks amazing. I also missed Josephine Skriver, at least for the Pink segment. I never really liked her walk, but she had a gorgeous face and a killer body, and seeing some of the other models who walked, far below her level, I think she definitely deserved her spot. And maybe Taylor Hill too, for her pretty face. I miss the times when this show was represented by pure models and Angels, not influencers or plus-size figures. Let‚Äôs be honest, they just don‚Äôt feel like part of the show. They don‚Äôt fit the iconic, angelic vibe that made Victoria‚Äôs Secret special. The show would have been so much better with those legends and with new, young, real models. Regarding the performances: what was going through their minds with that K-pop group? This year you can tell that they did put a lot of their dedication and thoughts and were truly invested in the process of making the stunning lingeries and the ornaments that go with each outfit work well together in an artistic, fashionable and conventional way, while trying to live up to many expectations people have for them in these recent years. Adriana is one of the original VS models that delivered the best performances walking down the runway, being breathtaking and surprisingly more glowing than ever while looking incredibly humble (I don't know, you just kinda get that beautiful yet down-to-earth vibe from her). You can tell how much Adriana still loves and appreciates the show that has contributed to her prominence in the industry. And the way we have the part where they interviewed Alessandra backstage is simply refreshing and nostalgic. Some of the new models have also done their jobs really well, not trying to overdo anything and simply concentrating on showing their flamboyant outfits and their charms as the models specifically selected by the VS team. Personally, I love the set that has Anok Yai in her gorgeous pink outfit the most. I think this set is kinda inspired by the showgirl theme considering their fluffy, feathery outfit embellisments and wings and their sparkling headdresses, which is such a visual feast to watch. The red set featuring Adut Akech as one of the models is also a chef's kiss. And Barbie looked simply gorgeous in the pink set. Overall, the 2025 Victoria's Secret fashion show is a must-watch for both the loyal fans and the new fans. They have tried their best to be inclusive while sucessfully creating some of the best, memorable lingerie sets in their history. They desever their recognition and to be praised this year üíö

I'm really sorry as a ONCE but this isn't their finest work. They weren't moving as intensely as other shows they've performed at but their vocals lacked stability WAY too many times here... I mean if you really think about it, the typical kpop method of performance relies heavily on backtrack and visual work so that's probably why they sound so different here and probably what they'd sound like if they didn't ever use backtrack. Some encore performances also sounded like this previously. It's why lots of kpop groups face criticism or hate, because encore stages strip all the backtrack and reveal true live vocal capabilities that can't be hidden with backtrack. That's what makes idols and singers COMPLETELY different. Singers should KNOW how to sing live and it's a common strategy to hear vocal improv in western artists' performances to prove that they are live singers. Yeah lip syncing still happens once in a while and it faces TONS OF BACKLASH in the west but for the most part, it's known that most famous singers are REAL VOCALISTS and don't need backtrack to sound good.

My feelings about this show are quite conflicting. I liked few things and hated several. Let's look at the positive points: 1- The photography was beautiful, the stage, the lighting, in short... everything was much better than last year. 2- Missy Elliot's show was impeccable, she did great as always. 3- Candice, Bela, Behati, Alessandra and Barbara were the ones who stood out the most. When Candice came in with that second look I was mesmerized by such beauty! Now the negative points: 1. I watch this show because of Adriana Lima, but damn! Sometimes I wonder if VS really likes her. Adriana looked stunning in the publicity campaign for this year's show, but the brand seems to take pleasure in sabotaging her! They always give her the worst clothes and a hairstyle that doesn't flatter her. What was that first look?! HORRIBLE! And now, punctuating what is up to her, it was the first time that I didn't like seeing her on stage. She was too stiff, looked uncomfortable and a little embarrassed. The impression it gave was that she worked her legs so much the day before the show that she couldn't walk properly. 2- Some wings were horrible and seemed absurdly heavy and uncomfortable. The white wing they gave to Gigi was the ugliest wing VS has ever made and one of the ones that Bela used was so clearly uncomfortable that the girl couldn't even walk properly, I even felt sorry for her, it was embarrassing to watch. 3- The round led lamp that moves in the center of the stage is beautiful and has an interesting effect, but at the Karol G show, when it was vertical and prevented us from seeing the models entering the runaway , it really bothered me. It seems that the team didn't know how to manage time and the models having to work around that thing gave me a strange vibe of a poorly managed show. 4- I've never seen such weak casting! What is happening to modeling agencies, have they lost their ability to find talent? I've never seen so many models without charisma and such a weak catwalk in all my life!
